<title>Update Compliance added to Windows Analytics suite of free services</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheWindowsClub/~3/3VPZiPC1xSY/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheWindowsClub/~3/3VPZiPC1xSY/</guid>
<description>&lt;p&gt;For IT departments, it is imperative to have a better understanding of the health of their devices before upgrading to a new OS experience. &lt;strong&gt;Windows Analytics&lt;/strong&gt; is a simple tool that offers data-driven insights to IT administrators to help them reduce the cost of deploying, servicing, and supporting Windows 10. It offers two solutions,&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Upgrade Readiness&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;Update Compliance&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;aligncenter size-large wp-image-90810&quot; src=&quot;http://news.thewindowsclubco.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Windows-Analytics-600x225.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;diagnostics&quot; width=&quot;600&quot; height=&quot;225&quot;/&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;h2 class=&quot;entry-title&quot;&gt;Windows Analytics: Update Compliance&lt;/h2&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;After remaining in preview mode for a while, the final version of Update Compliance is now out for release and ready to be tested. The final development is heavily influenced by feedback from the community.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to announce the General Availability of Update Compliance, as the newest addition to Windows Analytics. With the GA release, we will continue to make Update Compliance available for all Windows 10 desktops with Pro or higher licenses.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;ins class=&quot;adsbygoogle&quot; data-ad-client=&quot;ca-pub-5950002284129980&quot; data-ad-slot=&quot;6640627966&quot; data-ad-format=&quot;rectangle&quot;/&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Update Compliance is targeted to the IT pro who wants to gain a holistic view of all their Windows 10 devices – without any additional infrastructure requirements, mentioned a &lt;a href=&quot;https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/upgradeanalytics/2017/10/17/announcing-the-general-availability-of-windows-analytics-update-compliance/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;blog post&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Update Compliance will enable enables IT pros to do the following,&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Quickly identify devices with issues that need attention so as to make them ready for upgrade&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor the progress and status of Windows 10 updates carefully to assure complete compatibility&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;li&gt;Gain insights from any instances flagged by Windows 10 Defender Antivirus during its use.&lt;/li&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;While the current release of Update Compliance just provides general availability of the features that Microsoft had earlier released for public preview, it’s planning to make few big changes in the upcoming update. Stay tuned!&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Windows Analytics provides a suite of free services for analyzing the applications and devices to assess upgrade readiness. This helps in simplifying the validation processes to much an extent and reduce the efforts required to deploy, service and support Windows 10.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
